Extract entities from the corroboration document page below.

ENTITY ONTOLOGY (extract only these types):
{{ entity_ontology | tojson(indent=2) }}

KNOWN ENTITIES FROM CLIENT HISTORY (link to these where possible, do NOT re-extract them):
{{ known_entities | tojson(indent=2) }}

DOCUMENT SUMMARY (full document context):
{{ document_summary }}

PAGE {{ page_number }} SUMMARY:
{{ page_summary }}

Return a JSON object:
{
  "entities": [
    {
      "id":    "<type_prefix>_corr_<number>",
      "type":  "<entity type from ontology>",
      "label": "<short human-readable name>",
      "attributes": {
        "<attr>": "<value or null>"
      }
    }
  ],
  "entities_to_remove": []
}

Rules:
- Only extract entities that are NOT already in the known entities list above.
- If an entity from this page matches a known entity, do NOT re-extract it — you will be able to link to it by its existing id in the relationship step.
- Use the prefix "_corr_" in ids to distinguish corroboration entities (e.g. "person_corr_1").

{% else %}
Extract relationships from the corroboration document page below.

RELATIONSHIP ONTOLOGY (only use these types):
{{ relationship_ontology | tojson(indent=2) }}

ALL AVAILABLE ENTITIES (history KG + newly extracted from this document so far):
{{ known_entities | tojson(indent=2) }}

DOCUMENT SUMMARY (full document context):
{{ document_summary }}

PAGE {{ page_number }} SUMMARY:
{{ page_summary }}

Return:
{
  "relationships": [
    {
      "type": "<ONTOLOGY_TYPE>",
      "source": "<entity id>",
      "target": "<entity id>",
      "attributes": {
        "evidence": "<verbatim or paraphrased quote supporting this relationship>",
        "<attr_name>": "<attr_value or null>"
      }
    }
  ],
  "relationships_to_remove": []
}

Rules:
- "evidence" is REQUIRED on every relationship — never leave it empty.
- Include ALL attributes defined for the relationship type in the ontology.
- Do NOT include a "reasoning" field.
- You may link entities from the history KG to entities from this document.
{% endif %}
